<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-06-0209 </DOCNO><TEXT>Experiments in which polarized electrons are scattered from nucleon andnuclear targets are reviewed. The results provide unique informationabout the structure of hadronic matter as well as about the fundamentalelectroweak interaction. Emphasis is placed on possible new directionsin the field.</TEXT></DOC>